1. Introduction¶

Swire Coca-Cola is continually introducing innovative products into the market. Innovation diversifies product offerings, meeting evolving consumer trends. This strategy, marked by unique products and premium pricing, expands market reach and attracts new customers. It responds to technology changes and regulations, ensuring cost efficiency and compliance. Additionally, it rejuvenates sales and marketing. In essence, product innovation is essential for staying relevant, driving revenue, and sustaining long-term growth in a dynamic market.

So, Swire Coca-Cola wants to optimize its production planning and inventory management for these novel beverages. The challenge for Swire is to forecast the demand for these new products accurately to ensure optimal production quantities, prevent out-of-stock and overproduction, minimize costs, and maximize customer satisfaction. The Business problem is to accurately predict the weekly demand of the innovation products. The focus of our project will be on optimal production planning, cost minimization, and market location and date prediction.

The Analytical Problem is to forecast the details expected by the Swire for the 7 innovation products that are planned to be launched in the near future. The basic details of each of the new innovation products are provided so that it can be compared against the historical data and can be used to forecast the sales of the innovation products as close as possible to the real time sales.

The key factors for the Items are the Caloric Segment, Market Category, Manufacturer, Brand, Package Type and Flavor which will be used as the independent variables from the Previous years data to create a Forecast for the new innovation Products. So, the Target variable is the Dollar Sales/unit sales for the innovation products.

The goal of this EDA document is to uncover trends, clusters, and insights to help answer the questions proposed by Swire. Additionally, I want to be open to the possibility of discovering consistancies in the data to anticipate and solve more global questions about Swires innovation products. Thus enhancing the oppurtunity to be prepare the data for the modelling part along with gaining the insights on the Data provided.

Questions¶

The questions that we are expecting to answer through this EDA document is as follows:

  • How Caloric segment effects the sales and how it changes over the seasons
  • How the category of drink will impact the sales and which category is the favorite among the customers
  • How each of the catagory drinks will change according to time of the year
  • What are the top most Manufactures that have high sales for their innovation products
  • How the packaging effect the sales for the products
  • Will adding the demographic data help in creating a better model ?
  • Which segment of people are more likely to buy the Innovation Products

3. Loading Datasets and Data Description¶

3.1 Fact Market Demand Data¶

The main data file is the fact_market_demand data since that seems to hold the most value for answering the business problem. There are 10 fields and 24,461,424 rows. The columns are data, unit_sales, caloric_segment, category, manufacturer, brand, package, item, market_key and dollar_sales.

The date range is nearly three full years, spanning December 2020 to October 2023. The caloric segment is a categorical column with values Regular and Diet/light.

4.1 Handling Missing Data¶

Since both the Regular and Diet/light categories are equal we are unable to categorize the null value to any of the categories without disturbing the other data present. So, We can just replace that Null values with the string of 'Unknown', so that the data is not impacted.

In [ ]:
# Handling missing values

Fact_Demand_data['CALORIC_SEGMENT'].fillna('Unknown', inplace=True)

The Monthly Unit Sales Trend graph offers a clear visualization of sales performance over time, highlighting seasonal variations, trends, and any cyclical patterns present in the data. By observing peaks and troughs, we can pinpoint high-demand periods and potential sales slumps, aiding in inventory and promotional planning. This graph assists in forecasting future sales.

This clearly shows how various category types affect the sales ratio. However, SSD have the biggest impact on sales, comprising about 63.2% of total sales, making them the most influential category for customers.

In the upcoming innovation product ideas that the Swire-CC has provided, we can see that there are 2 products which comes under SSD category and 2 products which comes under Energy category, So the sales of these will be high with respect to the other 3 innovation products from the above pie chart.

6.6. Item Field Exploration¶

The content in the item column is a description of the item sold. This column is the longest has the longest text characters and the most unique values with 3,692. The description includes anonymized flavors and a repeat of the packaging. Since these are not the actual flavors, more analysis may be required to evaluate the value of this variable, aside from the coded flavor questions by Swire. Exploring the data we see that the SSD and Energy categories dominate the most unit sales.

The below graph represents the Dollar sales of items by date for top 5 ITEMS which high unit sales for overall period of time

In [ ]:
# Get Unit Sales data for top 5 items from Fact_Market_Demand Data from BigQuery

item_5_query = """
select distinct ITEM,
round(Sum(unit_sales),2) as unit_sales_total
from `swire.fact_market_demand`
group by ITEM
order by unit_sales_total desc
limit 5;
"""

ax.set_xticklabels(categories)

# Plotting using Seaborn

# Bar plot

All of the top 10 zipcodes with the highest population are from California, indicating that sales have a significant impact in this state. The zipcode 91331 has the largest number of people, over 70,000.

According to the data, California can be a major market for the product being sold as there are more people present. This has to be cross verified by connecting the demographics data to the fact_demand data, which wil be done in the next phase of Project.

7. Conclusion¶

This data set benefits greatly from disaggregating the values into its constituent parts to identify different trends and categories influencing unit sales. This EDA uncovered valuable popular caloric segments, beverage categories, and manufacturers. Seasonal trends and holiday sale spikes were also identified and will be useful in timing new innovation products. Brands, packages, and items are extensive and will help provide additional details to add to the other variables.

All the insights that are found can be used to mode forward in the modelling procss like finding that the Regular Caloric segment will lead to the higher number of sales rather than Diet/Light. This information can be trasformed and used when the forecasting of the new Innovative Products is done.

Also, from the exploration in the demographics data we have found that the Carifornia is a potential market as it is the most populated region, this has to be further explored by connecting the demographic dataset with the fact_demand dataset which will be concentrated on during the Modelling phase of the project.

Overall, for the forecast of the new Innovation products provided, we have considered that the Regular drinks are sold more when compared to the Diet/light drinks and also, the Energy and SSD type drinks are more sold than the other categories. These points are derived from EDA and will be used as the key points when the forecasting model is being created.
